# Auto-link website deploy

After changing inventory (`js/cars-data.js`), site pages, or styles, deploy when the user wants updates live:

```powershell
npm run deploy -- "Short commit message describing the change"
```

Requirements (one-time, already set up in this project):
- Git remote on GitHub (`origin`)
- Either Netlify linked to that GitHub repo (auto-deploy on push), **or** a `.env` file with `NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN` and `NETLIFY_SITE_ID` for CLI deploys

Never commit `.env`. Do not push unless the user asked for a live update or deploy setup.
